ZCZC OE63
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 102300 UTC
THROUGH FRIDAY EVENING AND SATURDAY A FAIRLY DEEP AREA OF
LOW PRESSURE 983 MBAR WILL BE CENTRED TO THE W OF
FITZROY. THE SCANDINAVIAN HIGH PRESSURE SYSTEM WILL
EXTEND A RIDGE ACROSS THE N SEA AND UK. PRESSURE WILL BE
LOW ACROSS THE MEDITERRANEAN SEA AND NEAR ICELAND. A
SIMILAR PRESSURE PATTERN LOOKS LIKE IT WILL PERSIST
THROUGH SUNDAY AND MONDAY ALTHOUGH THE RIDGE AXIS WILL
LIKELY DRIFT SLWY NWARDS ALLOWING A TIGHTER PRESSURE
GRADIENT TO FORM OVER THE SERN N SEA AND ENGLISH CHANNEL.
ON FRIDAY EVENING AND SATURDAY SE WINDS ARE EXP IN
FITZROY SOLE AND SHANNON. STRG SW WINDS ARE LIKELY AT
FIRST IN FAEROES AND SE ICELAND. ON SUNDAY AND MONDAY
STRG E OR SE WINDS ARE EXP IN LUNDY FASTNET SHANNON AND
ROCKALL AND PERHAPS BAILEY AND SE ICELAND LATER. WINDS
WILL MOD LATER ON MONDAY IN ROCKALL AND BAILEY
